arn.description: ARN of the Default Network ACL

defaultNetworkAclId.description:
Network ACL ID to manage. This attribute is exported from `aws.ec2.Vpc`, or manually found via the AWS Console.

The following arguments are optional:

egress.description: Configuration block for an egress rule. Detailed below.

ingress.description: Configuration block for an ingress rule. Detailed below.

ownerId.description: ID of the AWS account that owns the Default Network ACL

subnetIds.description: List of Subnet IDs to apply the ACL to. See the notes above on Managing Subnets in the Default Network ACL

tags.description: Map of tags to assign to the resource. If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.
